@anders_aslund It's quite extraordinary to be mad at people for not hating Russia enough.
The USSR and today's Russia are two very different countries.
And wasn't the USSR led by Nikita Khrushchev at the time, the former head of the Ukrainian SSR, the man who gave Crimea to Ukraine?

@unionjackflavor @MarkrKeogh @AnDrelceCold @SamRamani2 It's not tricky. If Russia attacks Ukraine's rail lines, that'd be fair game.

Schools, residential buildings, and electrical power for civilian areas nowhere near the front, is not fair game. Or the Kramatorsk rail station. Or hundreds of other civilian things.

This isn't hard.
